'From Squeak3.1alpha of 4 February 2001 [latest update: #3512] on 6 February 2001 at 12:38:52 pm'!"Change Set:		BluePrintCanvas-arDate:			6 February 2001Author:			Andreas RaabA little hack for Alan's BioVision talk allowing all morphs to be drawn in a blue print style. Watch the 'BluePrint.pr' project on Bob's superswiki."!FormCanvas subclass: #BluePrintCanvas	instanceVariableNames: ''	classVariableNames: ''	poolDictionaries: ''	category: 'Morphic-Support'!!BluePrintCanvas methodsFor: 'drawing-general' stamp: 'ar 2/6/2001 12:37'!drawMorph: aMorph	(self isVisible: aMorph bounds) ifTrue:[		self frameRectangle: aMorph bounds color: Color blue.	].! !!PasteUpMorph methodsFor: 'display' stamp: 'ar 2/6/2001 12:33'!useBluePrintCanvas: aBool	self isWorldMorph ifFalse:[^self].	worldState useBluePrintCanvas: aBool.	self fullRepaintNeeded.! !!WorldState methodsFor: 'canvas' stamp: 'ar 2/6/2001 12:34'!useBluePrintCanvas: aBool	aBool 		ifTrue:[self canvas: (BluePrintCanvas on: Display)]		ifFalse:[self canvas: Display getCanvas].! !